        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(doctor): surface multi-account default routing warnings in preview and lint",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\nFixes an issue where `openclaw doctor` preview and `openclaw doctor --lint` did not surface warnings about multi-account channels that lack explicit default routing or complete account-scoped bindings.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\nSurface `collectMissingDefaultAccountBindingWarnings` and `collectMissingExplicitDefaultAccountWarnings` through `collectDoctorPreviewNotes` (preview path) and `healthCheckIds` (lint path). Removed the duplicate direct calls from `doctor-config-flow`. The repair path (`openclaw doctor --fix`) routes the structured check through `runCoreContributionHealthRepair` inside `runGatewayServicesHealth`, matching the pattern used by `runBrowserHealth` for `browser-clawd-profile-residue`. Single source of truth across all three modes: preview, lint, and repair.\n\n## User Impact\nOperators running `openclaw doctor` preview, `openclaw doctor --lint`, or `openclaw doctor --fix` now see warnings when multi-account channels lack explicit default routing.\n\n## Evidence\n\n### Preview path (collectDoctorPreviewNotes) — 44 tests\n```\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/commands/doctor/shared/preview-warnings.test.ts --run\nTest Files  1 passed (1) / Tests  44 passed (44)\n```\nIncludes the new test: \"collects missing default account routing warnings in preview mode\" — verifies both \"accounts.default is missing\" and \"no explicit default is set\" warnings are surfaced for multi-account configs.\n\n### Lint/repair health check (doctor-core-checks) — 17 tests\n```\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/flows/doctor-core-checks.test.ts --run\nTest Files  1 passed (1) / Tests  17 passed (17)\n```\nIncludes \"reports missing default account routing as core health findings\" — verifies the structured health check produces `core/doctor/default-account-routing` findings with severity `warning`.\n\n### Repair-mode integration (doctor-health-contributions) — 49 tests\n```\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/flows/doctor-health-contributions.test.ts --run\nTest Files  1 passed (1) / Tests  49 passed (49)\n```\nIncludes the new regression test: \"routes default-account-routing check through gateway-services repair\" — verifies `runDoctorHealthRepairs` is called with `mode: \"fix\"` and `checks` containing `core/doctor/default-account-routing`.\n\n### Negative control: repair-mode regression caught\nWithout the `runCoreContributionHealthRepair` call in `runGatewayServicesHealth`, the regression test FAILS:\n```\nTest Files  1 failed (1) / Tests  1 failed | 48 skipped (49)\nFAIL  routes default-account-routing check through gateway-services repair\n→ expected runDoctorHealthRepairs to have been called (but it was not)\n```\nWith the fix restored, the test PASSES:\n```\nTest Files  1 passed (1) / Tests  1 passed | 48 skipped (49)\n```",
        "branch": "fix/doctor-preview-default-account-warnings",
